recent_note:
Meeting With SBL on Partnership aggrements. 
 Following the discussion between SBL’s CEO, Mr. Gopakumar, and the team from Heirs Technologies held on 5th Sept at Abuja, I wanted to provide a summary and confirm the next steps agreed upon: 
 Summary of Discussion: 
 
 We shared insights with Mr. Gopakumar regarding the e-Parliament implementation for the 36 State Assemblies, covering project viability, available funding sources, the pilot plan, and commercial aspects. 
 Heirs Technologies informed us that the System Study is anticipated to commence in approximately two weeks, and we have received the list of experienced personnel from your team to conduct the survey in the states. 
 Mr. Gopakumar emphasized the importance of our partnership, especially focusing on transitioning into capacity building and Post-Implementation Support for the client. 
 
 Agreed Next Steps: 
 
 The Representatives from SBL will join the Heirs Technologies team for the System Study, with a proposed sharing ratio of 50/50 between our teams. 
 Following the System Study, we will collaborate to review the commercials to determine the appropriate modules for the state houses of assembly.

name: POLCOOP (NEW SOFTWARE BUILD)
recent_note:
Summary of Meeting held at the police on Wednesday. June 21 at the Police with Mr. Lennox, Laura and Ejiro.

Feedback from the client were as follows:

1. Corporate website design, layout & content should be reverted to the previous design which was initially shared with them months ago. 
2. On the registration form, “ID card” should be changed to “warrant card.” 
3. Force/ AP number should remain the unique identifier for users when logging in, instead of IPPIS number. Reason being that the IPPIS number is currently being used as a backup means of verification by Laura, and they would like to keep it that way. 
And if at all IPPIS number should be used as a unique identifier, it means that we should have preloaded all IPPIS numbers on the system so that once the user enters their number, the system pulls up their details, and the user can then proceed with their registration. 

Client mentioned that soft copy of the IPPS number had been shared with AP in the past therefore that should be fully adopted
